cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.SI

This paper is about an online neural network editor that provides tools for visualizing, editing, and sharing neural networks. The primary focus is on the machine learning aspect of the tool, which suggests that it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, the paper also mentions collaborative features, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses the framework agnostic nature of the tool, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
